    <note>Weng(1) Yanguo [1956] His ancestors were Jingzhao residents. At the end of the Tang, they fled the rebellions and settled in  various parts of Fujian. His sixth generation ancestor moved to Chongan xian. He was Ting's [1955] uncle. The son-in-law of  Li(2) Hong(2) [1038], Weng(1) Shengzhi [4032], had the same generational name the same as Yanguo's grandsons and grandnephews. Hu(1) Hong [7252] was the cousin of his brother Yanshen's [4033] grandson-in-law, Hu(1) Yin [3402]. Yanshen's grandson, Mengzhi [4031], was the son-in-law of Li(2) Mixun's [1062] and Li(2) Mida's [1063] brother, Mizheng [3520]. Weng(1) Mengzhi and his wife, Li(2) Shi, lacked sons and Mengzhi used his cousin Chengzhi's [4030] son to be his heir. Fujian TZ, 147.37b-38a; Zhu Xi, WJ, 91.27a; XNYL, 1.22b-23a, 4.6b-7a, 5.3b-4a; Hu Yin, WJ, 26.41b; SHY:ZG, 42.52a, 53.136a-136b; Songshi yi, 7.2a. CBD, 3, 1979-80.</note>
